{"id":1583,"date":"2021-07-20T15:37:31","date_gmt":"2021-07-20T15:37:31","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/?p=1583"},"modified":"2021-07-22T13:43:11","modified_gmt":"2021-07-22T13:43:11","slug":"live-update-20-07-2021","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/2021\/07\/20\/live-update-20-07-2021\/","title":{"rendered":"Live Update 20\/07\/2021"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><span class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\"><strong>UPDATE<\/strong> <strong>13:24 22\/07\/2021:<\/strong><\/span> An issue has been identified where the Twilight Panthers were not receiving all their Void Damage buffs correctly. This issue has now been fixed.\u00a0<br><br><strong><span class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">UPDATE<\/span><\/strong> <span class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\"><strong>14:43 22\/07\/2021<\/strong><\/span><strong><span class=\"has-inline-color has-vivid-cyan-blue-color\">:<\/span><\/strong> We are currently addressing an issue concerning the start of the Lycaon event earlier today. There was a short window where a small number of players will have been able to collect rewards from the track immediately without completing the required souls. This issue has been fixed and the event will be turned back on shortly. A free bundle will be sent out to all players once the event is underway.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please note that the <strong>information below is not final<\/strong>, and certain aspects may be <strong>subject to change<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>CONTENTS<\/strong>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Alliance War &#8211; Bearer of the Curse &#8211; Lycaon<ol><li>Relic Overview<\/li><li>Milestone Rewards<\/li><li>Alliance Rewards<\/li><li>Chosen Titans and Boost Relic<\/li><\/ol><\/li><li>DoT Content Creators<\/li><li>Unofficial Social Channels<\/li><li>Official Social Channels<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>ALLIANCE WAR &#8211; <\/strong><strong><em>Bearer of the Curse &#8211; Lycaon<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https:\/\/lh5.googleusercontent.com\/dBJCZHi2aYvr_wowKFkQmuWx3oqbYWQu_39ygrhozs2AcoGj3WGIOwD8zzkZZJ7Po3ETYSc-BL4179POyR5vRmTDy-4D1E9DMpz35v6QyK-0OGn7g9U2ltymY999mg2yVfdbKCs7\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>STARTS:<\/strong> 22st July, 15:00 UTC<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong>ENDS:<\/strong> 26th July, 09:00 UTC<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u2018I have dealt with the winged Olympian just as you asked, Master.\u2019&nbsp; <\/em><strong><em>Lycaon <\/em><\/strong><em>whispered as he knelt before the Nexus altar.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>In the temple, a fantastic carved mural wrapped around the walls. The center altar enshrined a segment that showed an ancient and immortal being seated on a throne, with worshippers kneeling in exaltation.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>The eyes of the being in the mural flickered with corrupted void energy as a voice began to resonate in the chamber. Ethereal, ringing with harmony and dissonance simultaneously, the voice alone would be enough to bewitch even the most stalwart hero.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u2018The Pieces fall into place; only one obstacle remains. The Mages and their Olympian lapdogs scramble to halt my arrival &#8211;&nbsp; as we speak they are attempting to uncover the <\/em><strong><em>Divine Geode<\/em><\/strong><em>. Go my champion, and take it from them. With it, the wheels of fate will be unconstrained.\u2019<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Lycaon hid on a ridge overlooking a mine bustling with activity. Goliaths, Elementals and Gods were working tirelessly to excavate as <\/em><strong><em>Everdure <\/em><\/strong><em>stood overseer. The mere scent of the Olympians was enough to make Lycaon\u2019s blood boil. For thousands of years he bore the curse that Zeus set upon him, leaving him adrift with no kin or people to rule.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>It was then that a final stone was moved and a blinding light radiated from the quarry. Voices cried out from the mine, as the allies rushed to glimpse the legendary stone.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Tired of waiting, Lycaon roared and rushed down the slope &#8211; his body radiating with corrupted energy. Everdure raised his staff in the air and let out a beacon of light, calling waves of Apex Panthers to the field.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Lycaon, seeming more beast than man, broke out into a gallup on all four legs and tackled down a Panther. The panther whimpered and rolled away as Lycaon wiped his mouth and focused in on the Geode.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>The fallen panther\u2019s eyes flickered with void energy as it lumbered to its feet. Faster and more viscous than its brethren it took down an Apex Panther of its own, passing the corruption from a single bite. Before long, all of Everdure\u2019s panthers were reborn as <\/em><strong><em>Twilight Panthers<\/em><\/strong><em>, and the quarry was a sea of bloodshed.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>In the confusion, Everdure was all that stood between Lycaon and the Geode, as his allies fought, fled or died in the chaos.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>\u2018Ah, I can\u2019t\u2026 HELP ME!\u2019 a familiar voice cried out to Everdure. It was <\/em><strong><em>Grothurn<\/em><\/strong><em>, pinned under a Twilight Panther and fighting for his life.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>Time stood still as Everdure looked at the Geode behind him, Lycaon in front, and his son Grothurn to the side. Lycaon could not help but laugh.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>A few moments later, Everdure slew the panther and helped Grothurn to his feet. The Geode was gone, as was Lycaon.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><em>From across the battlefield Everdure and Gaia locked eyes. No words were exchanged, but the emotion they shared in that moment was unmistakable. Despair, sickly and thick, weighed down their hearts as they recognised the prophecy could not be stopped.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"985\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/notpromethus_skills3-985x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1595\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/notpromethus_skills3-985x1024.png 985w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/notpromethus_skills3-289x300.png 289w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/notpromethus_skills3-768x798.png 768w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/notpromethus_skills3.png 1320w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 985px) 100vw, 985px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>*Lycaon and his army have 50% resistance to the Crowd Control effects of Freeze and Terror<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Twilight Panthers &amp; Horde&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lycaon the cursed King of Arcadia, conjures Twilight Panthers and Twilight Horde units into battle:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1002\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/twilight2-1002x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1593\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/twilight2-1002x1024.png 1002w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/twilight2-294x300.png 294w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/twilight2-768x785.png 768w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/twilight2.png 1069w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1002px) 100vw, 1002px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Get these<strong> powerful Relics and more <\/strong>in the Milestone Rewards:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"699\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/algafungus-are-the-first-2-plants-1024x699.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1586\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/algafungus-are-the-first-2-plants-1024x699.png 1024w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/algafungus-are-the-first-2-plants-300x205.png 300w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/algafungus-are-the-first-2-plants-768x525.png 768w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/algafungus-are-the-first-2-plants.png 1199w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/ahh-scary-relics-1024x683.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1587\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/ahh-scary-relics-1024x683.png 1024w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/ahh-scary-relics-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/ahh-scary-relics-768x512.png 768w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/ahh-scary-relics.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Milestone Rewards<\/strong> are as follows<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\